data.meta_site_name: The Tuskegee Airmen: Soaring Towards a Double Victory
data.text:
“It was a very important historic development, to let African Americans fly airplanes, become pilots. That was like a barrier... for black men genetically smart enough, capable enough, skilled enough, to fly airplanes. So of course, racists said ‘no.’ But the Tuskegee Airmen showed that they were [capable]. So that was a very important victory for black rights.”

- Dr. Henry Louis Gates Jr.

Personal Interview - April 5th, 2014
